This article summarizes Vice President Mike Pence's remarks at the swearing-in ceremony of Dr. Tom Price as the new Secretary of Health and Human Services. Pence mentions that President Trump's priority is to repeal and replace the Affordable Care Act with a healthcare reform that lowers costs without increasing the size of the government. He praises Dr. Price for his background in medicine, healthcare, and budgetary issues, as well as his understanding of the challenges faced by state officials in programs like Medicaid. Pence highlights Dr. Price's experience as an orthopedic surgeon, as well as his leadership roles in the Georgia State Senate and Congress. He expresses confidence that Dr. Price will work towards President Trump's vision of a healthcare system that benefits all Americans.